<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-19-0190 </DOCNO><TEXT>Consideration of the extent to which the EEC is attaining its energy policyobjectives reveals an encouraging picture. A 20% growth in GDP for 1975-84was accompanied by a 5.7% advance in gross energy consumption and byzero increase in final energy demand. However, areas of concern remain.Progress has mainly been due to the rising price of energy and Communitysuccess will have been jeopardized by the recent slump in the oil price.Second, energy consumption in road transport has been growing rapidlywith no evidence of improved efficiency. Finally, transformation losseshave grown by one-third in a nine year period.</TEXT></DOC>